# Songs
Songs						KEY:Bard ~ Songs							CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality						SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/bard/									DESC:A bard performs songs from his songbook, in which are drawn from the bard song list. Unlike mages, bards keep a written account of his songs in his songbook. A bard begins play with 3 1st level bard songs of his choice. The bard also selects a number of additional 1st-level songs equal to his Charisma modifier to add to his songbook. Each time a character attains a new bard level, he gains two songs of his choice to add to his songbook. The two free songs must be of song levels he can perform. But like mages, the bard can also purchase songs for his songbook.																																																																										BONUS:SPELLKNOWN|CLASS=Bard;LEVEL=1|3+CHA		BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Bard Song Level Choice|2*(BardLVL-1)
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; To learn or perform a song, a bard must have a Charisma score equal to at least 10 + the song level (Cha 11 for 1st-level songs, Cha 12 for 2nd-level songs, and so forth). The Difficulty Class for a saving throw against a bard’s song is 10 + the song’s level + the bard’s Charisma modifier. In addition, a bard gains additional MP for having a high attribute (Charisma—see Table: Bonus MP per Day (by Spell Level) on the MP System page).
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; Songs are functionally categorized into two types: normal songs and maintained songs. Normal songs largely behave the same as spells, whilst maintained songs require the bard to actively maintain them (a free action) every round to keep their effects. Maintained songs effects end immediately if the bard is rendered helpless (ie: knocked unconscious or paralyzed), or otherwise prevented from taking a free action to maintain it each round. A bard may only have one maintained song active at a time, with maintained songs possessing vastly different traits than that of normal songs. They are as follows:
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; - The bard may perform normal songs while maintained songs are active. Any normal song that requires concentration to maintain still allows the bard to continue his maintained songs, but does not allow the bard to start a new song until he ends that song.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; - Creatures must be within the song’s range for the bard to maintain its effects. If a creature affected by a song leaves its range, the effect persists until the start of their next turn.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; - If a maintained song only targets a certain number of creatures, the bard may switch the target(s) of his maintained song once at the beginning his turn (provided that they are within the song’s range), immediately ending the song’s effects on the previous target(s).
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; - Any song that is maintained in which forces a saving throw on a creature does so every round (while within range) until the creature fails their saving throw that applies that song’s effect; all subsequent rounds then maintain that effect on the creature for the song’s duration or until dismissed.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; - If a creature is targeted by a maintained song and possesses spell resistance, a caster level check is imposed on the bard for every round until the bard passes, at which point all subsequent rounds do not require a caster level check for that song.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Songs.MOD																																														DESC:&nl; Starting a new song provokes an attack of opportunity and requires concentration checks as if they were spells.
# ----
Jingles					KEY:Bard ~ Jingles						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality						SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/bard/									DESC:Bards learn a number of jingles, or 0-level songs. These songs do not require the Perform skill like any other song, nor do they take up a song slot, but they do not consume MP and may be used again. Bards begin with 2 jingles and gain an additional jingle every four levels after 1st level.
Musical Power				KEY:Bard ~ Musical Power					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialAttack.Supernatural				SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/bard/									DESC:Starting at 1st level, a bard can empower and use any musical instrument or performance skill as a weapon. &nl; Using his ranks in the associated performance skill (perform (strings) for a harp) in place of his Base Attack Bonus, the bard can, as a standard action, make a ranged touch attack against a foe within %1 feet. This attack deals non-elemental damage equal to 1d4 + %2. &nl; Any instrument wielded by the bard can be enchanted as if it was a ranged weapon, applying any enhancement/enchantment onto this attack. If he does not use an instrument, in the case of Perform (Act), (Comedy), (Dance), (Oratory), (Sing), etc., he does not gain any bonuses on musical power. &nl; Rolling a natural 1 with an instrument causes it to gain the broken condition, receiving a -2 penalty on attack rolls and halving the bard’s skill bonus to Perform checks with that instrument. With an hour’s worth of work, a bard can repair a single instrument with the broken condition.|25+5*floor(BardLVL/2)|CHA
# Bardic Peformance
Bardic Performance			KEY:Bard ~ Bardic Performance					CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Supernatural				SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/bard/									DESC:A bard is trained to use the Perform skill to create magical effects on those around him, including himself if desired. He can use this ability for %1 rounds per day. Each round, the bard can produce any one of the types of bardic performance that he has mastered, as indicated by his level.|BardicPerformanceDuration																																																																																																					DEFINE:BardicPerformanceDuration|0	DEFINE:BardicPerformanceLVL|0	DEFINE:BardicPerformanceBonusDC|0	BONUS:VAR|BardicPerformanceDuration|4+CHA+2*(BardLVL-1)	BONUS:VAR|BardicPerformanceLVL|BardLVL
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Bardic Performance.MOD																																											DESC:&nl; Starting a bardic performance is a standard action, but it can be maintained each round as a free action.|PREVARLT:ClassProgression_Bard,7
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Bardic Performance.MOD																																											DESC:&nl; Starting a bardic performance is a move action, but it can be maintained each round as a free action.|PREMULT:2,[PREVARGTEQ:ClassProgression_Bard,7],[PREVARLT:ClassProgression_Bard,13]
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Bardic Performance.MOD																																											DESC:&nl; Starting a bardic performance is a swift action, but it can be maintained each round as a free action.|PREVARGTEQ:ClassProgression_Bard,13
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Bardic Performance.MOD																																											DESC:Songs and a bardic performance may be maintained at the same time. Changing a bardic performance from one effect to another requires the bard to stop the previous performance and start a new one as a standard action. A bardic performance cannot be disrupted, but it ends immediately if the bard is killed, paralyzed, stunned, knocked unconscious, or otherwise prevented from taking a free action to maintain it each round. A bard cannot have more than one bardic performance in effect at one time.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Bardic Performance.MOD																																											DESC:&nl; Each bardic performance has audible components, visual components, or both.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Bardic Performance.MOD																																											DESC:&nl; If a bardic performance has audible components, the targets must be able to hear the bard for the performance to have any effect, and such performances are language dependent. A deaf bard has a 20%% chance to fail when attempting to use a bardic performance with an audible component. If he fails this check, the attempt still counts against his daily limit. Deaf creatures are immune to bardic performances with audible components.
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Bardic Performance.MOD																																											DESC:&nl; If a bardic performance has a visual component, the targets must have line of sight to the bard for the performance to have any effect. A blind bard has a 50%% chance to fail when attempting to use a bardic performance with a visual component. If he fails this check, the attempt still counts against his daily limit. Blind creatures are immune to bardic performances with visual components.
# ----
Well-Versed					KEY:Bard ~ Well-Versed						CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary				SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/bard/									DESC:At 2nd level, the bard becomes resistant to the bardic performance of others, and to sonic effects in general. The bard gains a +4 bonus on saving throws made against bardic performance, sonic, and language-dependent effects.																																																																																																																																			ASPECT:SaveBonus|+4 bonus on saving throws made against bardic performance, sonic, and language-dependent effects.
# Versatile Performance
Versatile Performance			KEY:Bard ~ Versatile Performance				CATEGORY:Special Ability	TYPE:Bard Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary				SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/bard/									DESC:At 2nd level, a bard can choose one type of Perform skill. He can use his bonus in that skill in place of his bonus in associated skills. When substituting in this way, the bard uses his total Perform skill bonus, including class skill bonus, in place of its associated skill’s bonus, whether or not he has ranks in that skill or if it is a class skill. &nl; The types of Perform and their associated skills are: Act (Bluff, Disguise), Comedy (Bluff, Intimidate), Dance (Acrobatics, Fly), Keyboard Instruments (Diplomacy, Intimidate), Oratory (Diplomacy, Sense Motive), Percussion (Handle Animal, Intimidate), Sing (Bluff, Sense Motive), String (Bluff, Diplomacy), and Wind (Diplomacy, Handle Animal).																																																				BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Versatile Performance Skill Choice|1	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Versatile Performance Ability|floor((BardLVL-2)/4)|PREVARGTEQ:ClassProgression_Bard,6
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Versatile Performance.MOD						ASPECT:SkillBonus|You can use your bonus in Perform (Act) in place of your bonus in Bluff and Disguise.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Versatile Performance Skill Choice ~ Perform (Act)
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Versatile Performance.MOD						ASPECT:SkillBonus|You can use your bonus in Perform (Comedy) in place of your bonus in Bluff and Intimidate.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Versatile Performance Skill Choice ~ Perform (Comedy)
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Versatile Performance.MOD						ASPECT:SkillBonus|You can use your bonus in Perform (Dance) in place of your bonus in Acrobatics and Fly.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Versatile Performance Skill Choice ~ Perform (Dance)
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Versatile Performance.MOD						ASPECT:SkillBonus|You can use your bonus in Perform (Keyboard Instruments) in place of your bonus in Diplomacy and Intimidate.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Versatile Performance Skill Choice ~ Perform (Keyboard Instruments)
CATEGORY=Special Ability|Bard ~ Versatile Performance.MOD						ASPECT:SkillBonus|You can use your bonus in Perform (Oratory) in place of your bonus in Diplomacy and Sense Motive.|PREABILITY:1,CATEGORY=Internal,Versatile Performance Skill Choice ~ Perform (Oratory)
