Track						KEY:Beastmaster ~ Track						CATEGORY:Special Ability	SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/beastmaster/		TYPE:Beastmaster Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary										DESC:At 4th level, a beastmaster adds half his beastmaster level to Survival skill checks made to follow or identify tracks.																																																																																																																																																																																						BONUS:SITUATION|Survival=Follow or Identify Tracks|BeastmasterLVL/2
Woodland Stride				KEY:Beastmaster ~ Woodland Stride				CATEGORY:Special Ability	SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/beastmaster/		TYPE:Beastmaster Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary										DESC:Starting at 5th level, a beastmaster and his animal companion may move through any sort of undergrowth (such as natural thorns, briars, overgrown areas, and similar terrain) at their normal speed and without taking damage or suffering any other impairment. Thorns, briars, and overgrown areas that are enchanted or magically manipulated to impede motion will still affect the hunter and her animal companion.
Natural Savagery				KEY:Beastmaster ~ Natural Savagery				CATEGORY:Special Ability	SOURCELINK:https://www.finalfantasyd20.com/classes/core-classes/beastmaster/		TYPE:Beastmaster Class Feature.SpecialQuality.Extraordinary										DESC:Also, at 5th level, a beastmaster’s animal companion becomes more proficient and deadlier with their natural weapons. The animal companion gains a +1 bonus on attack and damage rolls with natural weapons, plus an additional +1 per three beastmaster levels after 5th.																																																																																																																																																													DEFINE:BeastmasterCompanionNaturalSavagery|0	BONUS:VAR|BeastmasterCompanionNaturalSavagery|1|TYPE=Boolean
